---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Surprising Words That Are Legal in Scrabble — ZA, QI, XI & More"
  description="Discover surprisingly valid Scrabble words that most players don't know exist. From ZA (11pts) to CWMS (11pts), these legal words will transform your game."
  keywords="surprising legal scrabble words, valid scrabble words, ZA scrabble, QI scrabble, unusual scrabble words, unexpected valid words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Surprising Words That Are Legal in Scrabble — ZA, QI, XI & More",
    "description": "Discover surprisingly valid Scrabble words that most players don't know exist. From ZA (11pts) to CWMS (11pts), these legal words will transform your game.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-30",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-legal-words-surprises" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is ZA a valid word in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, ZA is valid in both SOWPODS and TWL dictionaries. It's an informal word for pizza. Scoring 11 points (Z=10, A=1), it's one of the highest-scoring two-letter words and essential for dumping the Z tile in tight board positions." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What unusual two-letter words are valid in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Some surprisingly valid two-letter words include: QI (11pts, life force in Chinese philosophy), ZA (11pts, pizza), XI (9pts, Greek letter), XU (9pts, Vietnamese currency), JO (9pts, Scottish sweetheart), and KA (6pts, Egyptian spirit)." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Are there valid Scrabble words with no vowels?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Words with no standard vowels include: CRWTH (13pts, Welsh instrument), CWMS (11pts, plural of cwm/valley), TSK, and SH. Words using Y as vowel include GYM, FRY, GLYPH (14pts), NYMPH (15pts), LYMPH (15pts), and PYGMY (16pts)." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Surprising Words That Are Legal in Scrabble</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        "That's not a real word!" — a phrase heard at every Scrabble table. But the official dictionaries contain thousands of entries that don't look like English words at all. From ZA (pizza) to CWMS (valleys) to QI (life force), these surprising legal words are your secret weapon for high scores in tight spots.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">127</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid 2-letter words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">33</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Q-without-U words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Vowelless words</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">High-Scoring Two-Letter Shockers</h2>
      <p>These short words look fake but are completely legal. Memorise them — they'll save you dozens of times.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">ZA</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11pts — pizza</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">QI</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11pts — life force</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">XI</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts — Greek letter</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">XU</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts — Vietnamese coin</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">JO</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts — sweetheart</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">OX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts — bovine</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">AX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts — chopping tool</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">KA</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts — Egyptian spirit</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Q Without U — Game Changers</h2>
      <p>Drawing Q (10pts) without a U used to mean disaster. Not anymore — these Q-without-U words are tournament-legal:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
          <p class="text-purple-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Short Q-no-U</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QI (11pts), QOPH (18pts), QADI (14pts), QAID (14pts), QANAT (14pts), QAT (12pts)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
          <p class="text-purple-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Longer Q-no-U</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QINTAR (15pts), QINDAR (15pts), TRANQ (14pts), FAQIR (17pts), SHEQEL (18pts)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 QI Is Your Best Friend</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">QI (11pts) is the most important Q-without-U word. Short enough to play anywhere. On a DWS it's 22. On a TLS for the Q it's <span class="text-white font-medium">31 points for two tiles</span>.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Words With No Vowels</h2>
      <p>Stuck with all consonants? These vowelless words (using Y or none) are lifesavers:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">CRWTH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">CWMS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">NYMPH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">15pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">GLYPH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">LYMPH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">15pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">PYGMY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">16pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">TSK</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7pts</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Surprising Legals</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">AA (2pts):</span> A type of rough volcanic lava. Useful for parallel plays and vowel dumps.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">ZO (11pts):</span> A Tibetan yak hybrid. On a TLS for Z scores 31 for two tiles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">EUOUAE (6pts):</span> Longest word using only vowels — a medieval musical term. Great vowel dump in SOWPODS.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">AARRGHH (12pts):</span> An exclamation — valid in SOWPODS. Uses 7 tiles, potential bingo with doubled letters.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/q-words-without-u/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Q Words Without U — Complete List</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-without-vowels/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Without Vowels — Consonant-Only Plays</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/most-surprising-valid-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Most Surprising Valid Scrabble Words</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check if any word is valid — free, instant, no signup needed</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
